docs.abstract: “This should set off all kinds of red flags,” said one advocate, fearing the land grab will violate civil liberties. Others say it will harm the environment.
docs.snippet: “This should set off all kinds of red flags,” said one advocate, fearing the land grab will violate civil liberties. Others say it will harm the environment.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Trump administration is seeking new authority to acquire land near the Southern border with Mexico as part of its plan to quickly build immigration barriers, angering activists who said it would violate liberties and endanger the environment as a cost of fulfilling the president’s campaign promise.

headline.main: Trump Administration Wants More Control Over U.S. Lands for Border Wall
headline.print_headline: Border Agency Wants Control Over Lands Along Route of Wall

docs.abstract: A Senate report concluded that $800 million worth of fentanyl pills were shipped to the United States by Chinese sellers through mail system loopholes.
docs.snippet: A Senate report concluded that $800 million worth of fentanyl pills were shipped to the United States by Chinese sellers through mail system loopholes.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Nearly $800 million worth of fentanyl pills were illegally sold to online customers in the United States over two years by Chinese distributors who took advantage of internet anonymity and an explosive growth in e-commerce, according to a Senate report released on Wednesday.

headline.main: Online Sales of Illegal Opioids from China Surge in U.S.
headline.print_headline: $800 Million in Illegal Opioids, and All Smugglers Needed Was the Correct Postage

docs.abstract: The New Hampshire state court said drug searches by federal and local authorities at a checkpoint 90 miles from the U.S. border violated state and federal laws.
docs.snippet: The New Hampshire state court said drug searches by federal and local authorities at a checkpoint 90 miles from the U.S. border violated state and federal laws.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A state court in New Hampshire has ruled that the arrests of several people last summer who were charged with drug possession at an immigration checkpoint set up by the United States Border Patrol were unconstitutional under state and federal law.

headline.main: Drug Arrests at Immigration Checkpoint Violated Constitution, New Hampshire Court Finds

docs.abstract: Marina Gross, the American interpreter during President Trump’s meeting with President Vladimir V. Putin of Russia, is facing calls from Congress to testify.
docs.snippet: Marina Gross, the American interpreter during President Trump’s meeting with President Vladimir V. Putin of Russia, is facing calls from Congress to testify.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Marina Gross, the only other American in the room during President Trump’s meeting on Monday with President Vladimir V. Putin of Russia, was the interpreter for Laura Bush at the Russian resort of Sochi in 2008 and interpreted for former Secretary of State Rex W. Tillerson in Moscow in 2017. She appears to live in an apartment in Arlington, Va., is an employee of the State Department and is, unsurprisingly, fluent in Russian.

headline.main: Who Heard What Trump Said to Putin? Only One Other American
headline.print_headline: She Was in the Room, but Don’t Count on Her to Talk
